aside:
	- Programmer Anarchy
	- why is the 'duct tape programmer' winning?
	- ATDD, Fit or Gherkin
	- Test-Driven Development —Kent Beck. Revisit it.
		- Avoid testing implementation details, test behaviors.
		- Test the public API.
	- Unit Test = Unit of isolation is the test, not the class. Kent Beck.
	- "Dependency is the key problem in software development at all scales" —Beck
	- Code Smells
		- Duplicated Code, Parallel Inheritance Hierarchies
		- Long Method, Lazy Class
		- Large Class, Speculative Generality
		- Long Parameter List, Message Chains
		- Divergent Change, Inappropriate Intimacy
		- Shotgun Surgery, Data Class
		- Feature Envy, Redused Bequest
		- Data Clumps, Comments
		- Primitive Obsession, Temporary Field
		- Switch Statements, Middle Man
	- POJO etc, objects without any dependencies. "Leaf objects".
	- ATDD = Acceptance TDD
